headline: Nestle and Keurig want you to make iced coffee at home instead of paying a barista. That’s harder than it looks
summary: Iced coffee just isn’t the same when you make it at home. It quickly waters down, tastes bitter and simply doesn’t emulate what you pay a barista upwards of $8 for.
